						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up behind the Rāmalingasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 1th century.</p>						

						<p>It mentions a chief of the Telugu Chōḻa family bearing the titles <hi rend="italic">Uṟeyūr-pura paramēśvara</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Iḻ[ivi]ṭṭi-paṟeghōshaṇa.</hi> The emblem of the family was lion and their banner had the figure of a tiger on it. The epigraph is fragmentary and damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
